 {"id":"bd-b17","title":"Implement error masking (mask_error_details)","description":"# Implement Error Masking (mask_error_details)

## Background
Python FastMCP provides `mask_error_details` server configuration to hide internal error details from clients in production. This prevents leaking sensitive information (file paths, stack traces, internal state) while still providing useful error messages to developers during development.

## Requirements

### Server Configuration
```rust
impl ServerBuilder {
    /// Enable/disable error detail masking
    ///
    /// When enabled (default in production), internal error details are hidden:
    /// - Stack traces removed
    /// - File paths sanitized
    /// - Internal state not exposed
    /// - Generic "Internal error" message returned
    ///
    /// When disabled (development mode), full error details are returned.
    pub fn mask_error_details(self, enabled: bool) -> Self

    /// Configure based on environment
    /// Automatically masks in release builds or when FASTMCP_ENV=production
    pub fn auto_mask_errors(self) -> Self
}

// Usage
let server = ServerBuilder::new("api", "1.0")
    .mask_error_details(true)  // Always mask
    .build();

// Or auto-detect
let server = ServerBuilder::new("api", "1.0")
    .auto_mask_errors()  // Mask based on environment
    .build();
```

### Error Masking Behavior
```rust
impl McpError {
    /// Apply masking to error before sending to client
    pub fn masked(&self, mask_enabled: bool) -> McpError {
        if !mask_enabled {
            return self.clone();
        }

        match self.code {
            // Preserve client errors (4xx equivalent)
            ErrorCode::InvalidRequest |
            ErrorCode::InvalidParams |
            ErrorCode::MethodNotFound => self.clone(),

            // Mask internal errors
            ErrorCode::InternalError |
            ErrorCode::ServerError(_) => McpError {
                code: self.code,
                message: "Internal server error".into(),
                data: None, // Remove all internal data
            },
        }
    }
}
```

### What Gets Masked
- Stack traces
- File paths (e.g., `/home/user/project/src/handler.rs:42`)
- Database error details
- Environment variables mentioned in errors
- Internal state dumps
- Exception chain details

### What's Preserved
- Error code (for programmatic handling)
- Generic error category
- Request ID (for correlation)
- User-safe error messages

